    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels at MRL 2. Discretization error exceeded requirements at Gradation 3. Validation results demonstrate mean absolute error of 8.3% for NIH across all operating points, within the acceptance band. The six remaining factors were addressed at Gradation 1 consistent with MRL 2 requirements for a Class II device. The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD model provides sufficient evidence to support the COU decision regarding worst-case hemolysis identification for the CPB centrifugal pump.",
